Package database

Class SaveCSV

java.lang.Object
database.SaveCSV
public class SaveCSV extends Object
The SaveCSV class provides static methods to save various entities into CSV files. Each method retrieves data from the respective controllers and writes to a corresponding CSV file. CSV files are saved in the src/database/ directory

    • saveProject

      public void saveProject()
      Save details of all BTOProjects as the ProjectList.csv CSV file. Columns include project name, manager NRIC, project neighbourhood, units and prices for each flat type, opening and closing dates, available officer slots, visibility, enqauiries and applications. assigned officers and registrations

    • saveManagers

      public void saveManagers()
      Save details of all Managers as the ManagerList.csv CSV file. Columns include name, NRIC, age, marital status and password

    • saveApplicants

      public void saveApplicants()
      Save details of all Applicants as the ApplicantList.csv CSV file. Columns include name, NRIC, age, marital status and password

      public void saveOfficers()

    • saveEnquiries

      public void saveEnquiries()
      Save details of all Enquiries as the EnquiryList.csv CSV file. Columns include enquiry ID, applicant NRIC, project name, message, response and the enquiry status

    • saveBTOApplications

      public void saveBTOApplications()
      Save details of all BTO Applications as the ApplicationList.csv CSV file. Columns include application ID, applicant NRIC, project name, flat type, application status and withdrawal status

    • saveRegistrations

      public void saveRegistrations()
      Save details of all Registrations as the RegistrationList.csv CSV file. Columns include registration ID, officer NRIC, project name, registration date and registration status
